node.text: Newly minted citizens include medical staff including doctors, nurses, as well as cleaning staff, cashiers and garbage collectors, according to a statement released last week by France''s citizenship minister Marlène Schiappa. "These frontline workers responded to the call of the nation. The country pulled through thanks to them," Schiappa said in a statement. Under this pandemic initiative, France took in 12,012 new nationals out of more than 16,300 people who sent applications for citizenship, in a process that includes interviews & tests. Residency requirement was decreased from 5 to 2 years.
